DOCS_modelChunk = [{"ty":"is","ibi":1,"s":"April 19, 2020 @ 3:00 PM 
Hello Oiler Families, 
Happy Sunday, April 19th! I hope you’ve enjoyed your spring break and are looking forward to reconnecting with your teachers as we continue our journey with the Flexible Education Program (FEP).
It is disappointing that we will not end our school-year and move into summer in the normal way. However, we should be very proud of how we have remained positive and worked together to stay safe and healthy as we have put our FEP in place. Stay encouraged, keep practicing safe and healthy habits and continue your hard work and we will have this crazy time behind before we know it. Our West Hardin resilience has been inspiring! Keep it up!
As we wind down spring break, I have some reminders for you.:
1. Week 4 packets for April 20– 24 were distributed along with week 3 packets on April 7th.
2. Weeks 5 and 6 packets will be available beginning Tuesday, April 28th.
3. Keys for Student success:
a. 	Students do their assignments.
b.	Students and/or parents notify their teacher if help is needed.
c. 	Students and/or parents maintain open communication with their teacher(s).
TEA’s next statewide conference call with school district’s is next Tuesday at 3:00 PM. We expect to get some guidance on closing out the school year. Our leadership team will meet after the TEA call for further discussions about all end of the year activities. We will put out information as soon as decisions are made. 
Thank you for all you have done to help keep our students and community safe. Please continue to take all the recommended safety precautions to stop the spread of the coronavirus. 
Please continue to pray for our country, state and community. 
Thank you,
Jim Armstrong, Superintendent
 



April 17, 2020 @ 1:50 PM

Hello Oiler Families,

I hope you had a great spring break that included some rest and relaxation. 

At his noon press conference today, Governor Abbot extended the school closure through the end of the year. That means we will continue to have school using our Flexible Education Program (FEP).

To our seniors, please know that we are still committed to having a graduation and a prom for you. We obviously do not know what that will look like at this time but will continue to work on making that happen.

TEA’s next statewide conference call with school district’s is next Tuesday at 3:00 PM. We expect to get some guidance on closing out the school year. Our leadership team will meet after the TEA call for further discussions about all end of the year activities. We will put out information as soon as decisions are made.

Thank you for all you have done to help keep our students and community safe. Please continue to take all the safety precautions to stop the spread of the coronavirus.

Please continue to pray for our country, state and community.

Thank you,
Jim Armstrong, Superintendent



April 10, 2020 @ 8:00 PM

FEP Update

Happy Easter to all of our Oiler Community. Rejoice in the blessing of Easter!

Grading Information

The Texas Education Agency (TEA) requires students to “demonstrate mastery” of the Texas Essential Knowledge and Skills (TEKS) in order to receive course credit or promotion to the next grade level. This requirement has not changed despite this challenging COVID-19 situation.
 
As you know, with cooperation between teachers, parents and students, we have implemented our Flexible Education Program (FEP). The goal of the FEP is to continue the teaching and learning process . During the FEP, student work will be evaluated. Administrators and teachers are working to determine the most equitable and meaningful way to promote learning and to evaluate student work. That work is ongoing, but where possible, we want to clearly define the expectations for student success. Students will be successful when…
1. Students do their assignments.
2. Students and/or parents notify their teacher if help is needed.
3. Students and/or parents maintain open communication with their teacher(s).

- West Hardin School (circle drive) – for Residents of Batson and Saratoga
- Solid Rock Church – for Residents of the Neighborhood and Outlaw Bend
 - Thicket Church of God – for Residents of Felps Cemetery Rd. and North to 
 Eastwood Village 
- Encounter Church in Votaw – for Residents of Barney Castle Rd. and Northward 
Packets for week 3 and 4 will be available for pick up on Tuesday, April 7th. Since everyone could use a break, we will be having Spring Break as scheduled April 13 – 17. Yaaaahoooo! Therefore, the week 3 packet is for April 6-10 and the week 4 packet is for the week after Spring Break, April 20-24. After next week, there will be no more work distributed until Tuesday, April 28th. 
Students who have Chromebooks will be expected to get assignments and return assignments electronically. If you have any questions about this, please contact Mr. Smith or Ms. Atkinson.
Students picking up packets may return their completed packets as follows:
- Put it in the designated drawer in the file cabinet where it was picked up.
- Email it to teachers 
As a reminder, week 1 and 2 packets are still available in the file cabinet at the school until Sunday. 
We will provide information about grading by the end of next week.
We do not have staff that are keeping regular hours at the school. If you need to contact school personnel, please use email. A staff directory can be found at www.westhardin.org under the “parent” tab.

March 31, 2020 @ 6:30 P.M.
FEP Update:
1.	Governor Abbott has extended school closures until May 4th.
2.	We will continue to provide remote instruction. Your teachers will continue to communicate with you about your instruction.
3.	Attention 7th and 8th grade parents: We will be handing out Chromebooks to 7th and 8th graders on Thursday b/t 3 - 7 p.m. in the circle drive in front of the school. See recent FB post from Mr. Smith for details.
4.	We are scheduled to have additional hot-spots up and running at Batson Prairie Baptist Church and FBC, Saratoga by Friday. Thicket Church of God is scheduled for Tuesday. We are waiting for confirmation for 1 more location. The goal is to have all hot spots up and running by next Friday, April 10th. 
5.	We will start a community outreach campaign tomorrow. We'll be using a mutli-media approach to encourage students, staff and community to adhere to the behaviors needed in order to stop the spread of the coronavirus. This will be a statewide campaign. We’re in this together. Please share with everyone you can as you receive the information. 
6.	Please continue to role model for your children, neighbors and community the safe and healthy behaviors needed to stop the spread of this virus.
7.	Continue to pray for everyone, everywhere. 
Thank you,
Jim Armstrong, Superintendent


March 29, 2020 @ 9:10 PM
Hello Oiler Families,
I apologize for the late post but I wanted you to have this information as soon as possible.
As the threat of the Coronavirus increases, it becomes a greater risk to everyone in our community. In an effort to better protect us all, we are making another adjustment.
When we deliver meals tomorrow at the designated locations, we will be delivering 5 days of meals instead of 2 days of meals. We will also deliver packets as planned.
After tomorrow, in consideration of the health and safety of all students, staff and community, we will be suspending all meal services until further notice.
This decision was a difficult one but it was made with the best interest of our entire West Hardin community at heart.
We will continue providing instruction but in a manner that will require less person to person contact. We will continue to place packets in the file cabinet in front of the school. The week 2 packets will be available in the cabinet on TUESDAY morning.
There is now a second file cabinet out front designated for the return of completed packets. The drawers are clearly labeled for different grade levels.
High School students can use the hot-spots at either the campus or at the Encounter church in Votaw. We will be adding more remote hot-spots as soon as possible.
We will update any changes to the instructional program in the coming days.
Please continue to pray for our country, state, community, and especially our HJ neighbors.
Thank you,
Jim Armstrong, Superintendent


March 29, 2020 @ 2:20 PM
Beginning Monday, March 30, 2020
Meal and Packet Pick-up Locations are as follows:
1) Residents of Batson - Batson Prairie Baptist Church 
2) Residents of the Neighborhood and Outlaw Bend - Solid Rock Church 
3) Residents of Saratoga - First Baptist Church, Saratoga 
4) Residents of Felps Cemetery Rd. and North to Eastwood Village - Thicket Church of God 
5) Residents of Barney Castle Rd. and Northward - Encounter Church in Votaw
 


March 28, 2020 @ 8:00 PM

* Flexible Education Program (FEP) Quick Facts
 Revised 3-28-2020
Effective Date Monday, March 30, 2020
1) FEP meals and packet pick up/drop off will be on Mondays (2 days of meals) and Wednesdays (3 days of meals) at the locations listed below.
2) Pick up time for both days at each location is 9:30 – 10:30 in the morning.
3) Pick up locations are determined by a student’s residence; please pay attention to the descriptions below.
4) Pay attention to the information about what specific location to use for your student(s). Your student’s meals and/or packets can ONLY be picked up at the designated location as described below.
 5) Meals and packets will not be delivered along the bus route but only at the locations listed below.
6) If you have communicated back and forth with the school and confirmed meals and packets for this coming week, they will be provided at the one specific location for your student as described under the Flexible Education Program banner below. Lists will be used for verification. 
6A) Parents may pick up meals and packets for other students as long as #6 above has been satisfied and the other students are on our list. 
7) If you have NOT communicated back and forth with the school and confirmed meals and packets for this coming week, they will not be available for you on Monday. Lists will be used for verification.
8) If you would like to participate beginning Wednesday, please contact the school on Tuesday morning between 8:00 a.m. and 12:00 p.m. to make arrangements for Wednesday pick up. Call (936) 274-5061 ext. *402 or email at sridge@westhardin.org. 
9) Pick up Locations – Pay attention to the description of who should pick up at each location.

March 27, 2020 @ 10:00 PM

Hello Oiler Families,

Thank you again for your ongoing support as we manage our way through this continuing health crisis together. As the circumstances keep changing, we have tried to adjust our program in order to comply with the latest health and safety recommendations for our students, staff and community. New information received today requires flexibility in our program once again.

Due to the “Stay at Home” order imposed today by Hardin County Judge Wayne McDaniel and surrounding county judges, West Hardin CCISD will extend our school closure until April 10, 2020. We will continue to implement our Flexible Education Program (FEP) during this time, but will do so with additional adjustments put in place. As we announced earlier this week, beginning Monday, March 30th, we will use our buses to deliver meals and packets to our communities. The additional adjustment includes delivery at one central location within each community. We will set up delivery locations in Batson, Saratoga, Thicket, Votaw, and the Neighborhood/Outlaw Bend. Parents will be able to drive-thru and pick up meals and packets and drop off completed packets. 

We realize that this adjustment comes even before we could implement the adjustment we announced earlier this week. We can only thank you for being so flexible in our partnership to support our children. We are West Hardin Strong and we will get through this together. We are working through the details and will get the information out to you as soon as possible.

March 26, 2020 @ 7:10 PM
Flexible Education Program Update for March 26th: 
Exciting News! We finished installing a remote WiFi “HotSpot” at the Encounter Church in Votaw. Students can access the internet just be pulling into the parking lot. Any WH device should automatically connect to the internet when in range. Thank you to Encounter Church for supporting this partnership. You Rock! By the way, students can do the same thing in the school parking lot.
Reminder for WH Parents: School folks called all parents of WH students today about the FEP adjustments that were announced yesterday. If you did not receive a call, we do not have a working phone number for you. Please contact us between 8:00 am -12:00 pm tomorrow with the following information:
Parent name
Student(s) name
Grade level of all students
Whether or not you need meals
Number of meals needed
Phone number
Email address.
You may call (936) 274-5061 ext. * 402 OR email Shannon Ridge at sridge@westhardin.org 
Children who live in WH but do not attend WH schools or are not of school age may participate in the meal program. To participate, parents must email the requested information to Shannon Ridge at sridge@westhardin.org by Friday, March 27th at 12:00 noon. Information needed:
Parent first and last name
Student(s) name
Physical Address
Phone number
Email address
Parents will be contacted after the information is received.
 
Attention Parents/Students who attend WH school but do not live in the district:
Packets will be available for pick up in the filing cabinet in the front of the school.
Packets can be dropped off in the bin next to the filing cabinet in the front of the school beginning next Monday (March 30th).
If you need meals, the district in which you live should supply them.
 Thank you for your continued prayers and support.


March 25, 2020 @ 10:25 PM
See additional information related to the FEP adjustments announced earlier this evening:
Packets will also be returned via buses each Monday.
Packets will still be available for pick up from the file cabinet on campus for students who live outside the district or otherwise need to pick up packets. 
We will post more details as they become available. Remember that parents will be contacted and be able to ask any unanswered questions at that time. Be sure that school phone numbers are not “accidentally” blocked.


March 25, 2020 @ 8:00 PM
Attention! Attention! FEP Adjustments Announced
In order to better serve our children and community while following the health and safety recommendations regarding COVID-19, we are making the following adjustments to our Flexible Education Program beginning Monday, March 30th.
Meals and packets will be delivered on our school buses on the regular bus routes. 
Delivery will take place at the student’s normal bus stop.
2 days of meals will be delivered on Mondays; 3 days of meals will be delivered on Wednesdays.
School work packets will be delivered on Mondays.
Students who do not normally ride the bus will be put into the appropriate route based on where they live. 
We will be calling all parents to confirm the number of meals needed and grade level of students living at that address.
Children who live in WH but do not attend WH schools or are not of school age may participate in the meal program. To participate, parents must email the requested information to Shannon Ridge at sridge@westhardin.org by Friday, March 27th at 12:00 noon.
 Information needed:
o Parent first and last name
o Student(s) name
o Physical Address
o Phone number
o Email address
Parents will be contacted after the information is received.

March 24, 2020 @ 1:30 PM
Attention Parents: Extra packets for elementary and middle school are now available for pick up in the file cabinet outside the front door of the school (off the circle drive). All assignments for elementary (PK-6th grade) and middle school (7th-8th grade) are the same by grade level. In HS, each student's schedule is different and a packet must be individually put together. HS packets will be placed in the file cabinet upon request. To request HS packets contact Ms. Atkinson at aatkinson@westhardin.org or Mr. Smith at msmith@westhardin.org. Thank you.


March 23, 2020 @ 7:15 PM
 
Flexible Education Program (FEP) Update: We have exciting news and disappointing news. The exciting news is that we gave out 4218 meals this morning and that a high percentage of student packets were picked up! The disappointing news is our food supplies ran out before we were able to meet the need of all of our community. We more than quadrupled our preparation from last week and it still was not enough. We offer our sincerest apology! 
 
As we learn new information during this ever-changing situation, we will be considering possible adjustments to make the FEP run more effectively and efficiently. If any adjustments are made, we will share the information as soon as it is available. Stay tuned through our social media and website.
 
I also want to clarify some information. The District does not need to meet a “quota” of meals served in order to get reimbursed for what we do serve. No matter the number served, we will get reimbursed for all of them. Thank you to all who were showing up to support us while thinking we had to reach a quota. This is not meant in any way to discourage folks from coming, I just wanted to clarify the information. Reminder: ALL children 18 and under and an accompanying adult are eligible for meals.
 
Thank you again for your continued patience and prayers.
 
Jim Armstrong, Superintendent


March 22, 2020 @ 6:00

Hello West Hardin Families,
This is Jim Armstrong. I want to remind you about how our Flexible Education Program will work beginning tomorrow, Monday, March 23rd.

Meals and school packets can be picked up at the same time. Pick up for both will be ONLY on Monday’s. They will receive 5 breakfasts, 5 lunches and student work for one week. Folks can pick up packets for as many students as they would like. Meal pick up will be in the front circle drive and packet pick up will be in the main parking lot where the morning school buses drop off.

Residents of Batson should arrive at school between 9:30-10:30; Residents of Saratoga between 10:30- 11:30 and Residents of Votaw and Thicket between 11:30-12:30.
We hope that scheduling pick up times will help things run more smoothly.
Thank you...Go Oilers!

March 20, 2020 @ 5:00 PM
 
Hello West Hardin Family,

As we end this first week of “adjusting on the move,” I am once again in awe of our school staff and community. We are in the midst of another crisis, a crisis this time where the circumstances are changing rapidly. My awe comes from the continued resilience shown by our entire community. Whatever happens, we stand together united to take care of our children and each other.
 
On behalf of the School Board and our West Hardin staff, thank you for your continued patience and prayers as we develop and adjust our Flexible Education Program (FEP). We are proud to serve in and with the Oiler community.

Reminder: On Monday, March 23rd we are adjusting our FEP: 
We will begin supplying all meals for the week on Mondays (in front circle drive).
We will hand out and take up instructional packets at the same time you come for meals (at the morning SCHOOL BUS drop off in the main parking lot). 

Students do not need to be in the vehicle to receive meals or packets.
Drivers may pick up school work packets for as many students as they would like.

March 17, 2020 6:00 PM
 Flexible Education Program for WHCCISD
Hello Oiler Family, 
We are in the middle of an extraordinary situation because of the health threat from the coronavirus. It is a challenge unlike any we have faced before. But, so was Hurricane Harvey at the time. And we came together as a community and not only survived Harvey, but came out stronger on the other side. We will meet this current challenge together and do the same. 
So, how are we going to have school without the school buildings? Thanks to the work of a lot of folks, we have a plan. And we need your help to execute that plan. 
We have developed a Flexible Education Program (FEP) that involves both our instructional and food service programs. We will use the FEP while we are not able to implement our traditional programs on campus. We are going to have school and feed students in the best way we can.
The FEP general information is listed below. 
1) At this time the FEP will be in place until April 3rd. We will reevaluate our situation on Friday, April 3rd for the next week. We will reevaluate every Friday thereafter for the next week.
2) More specific information about the delivery of school work will be provided by the campus principal and/or teacher by the end of this week.
3) We are investigating the possibility of remote “hot spots” for various locations in our communities. Stay tuned.

6) Initially, we will provide drive-thru food service at the high school for breakfast and lunch as follows:
a. Trial runs will be Thursday and Friday of this week at the times listed below; after that
b. Monday – Friday
c. Breakfast 7:30 – 8:30
d. Lunch 10:30 – 12:00
e. All children 18 and under and their accompanying adult are eligible for meals
f. All meals are free to all children their accompanying adult
g. Child or accompanying adult may pick up
h. Meals will be grab and go
i. Meals will meet USDA guidelines
7) All extracurricular and after school activities are suspended until further notice
8) All community after school activities are suspended until further notice

Thank you for your support and flexibility!
"It's an Oiler State of Mind"
Jim Armstrong, Superintendent of Schools 

MARCH 16 2020 5:30 PM

To our Oiler Family
The health and safety of our students, staff and community is our first priority. In an abundance of caution and in anticipation of a disaster declaration and emergency order by Hardin County and surrounding county judges, West Hardin CCISD is suspending classes for the remainder of this week. The judge’s order is expected by noon tomorrow. We will provide additional information after that time. 
Again, school is suspended for the remainder of this week (March 16-20). Look for more information tomorrow afternoon. 
Thank you for your patience as we navigate these uncharted waters."
"It's an Oiler State of Mind"
Jim Armstrong, Ed.D.
Superintendent of Schools
